S|# 28 · Dashboard / Home (System)|> The landing/overview screen of Mission Control. Appears as `dashboard-home.md` in the creator's own Briefings folder (screenshot 181510).
S|Purpose|The default landing view when you open a workspace's Mission Control — a top-level overview that orients the owner before they dive into the dec Queue. Where the **dec Queue** is the action funnel ("the 7 things that need me"), the Dashboard/Home is the at-a-glance status of the whole operation.
S|What it covers (inferred)|- A morning overview: system health, agents live, what was handled overnight, and a pointer into the dec Queue. // - Summary tiles likely pulling from across the app: pending decisions, posts awaiting ap, tasks in rv, software items needing rv, inbox state, revenue/consulting status. // - Per-workspace, so it re-themes and re-scopes when you switch workspaces.
S|Relationship to other screens|- Sits above the Command Center group; feeds the owner into **dec Queue** (`01`), **Task Board** (`02`), and the anl surfaces. // - Conceptually the "home" that the global top bar's status indicators (System healthy, agents live) summarize. // > **Confidence: Inferred.** This page is named in the creator's Briefings folder (`dashboard-home.md`) but was **not** shown as a dedicated UI screenshot, and "Dashboard"/"Home" was not consistently visible in the captured sidebars (most crops show the Com